## Installation

### Quick Start
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/cdetheme.git
cd cdetheme

# Start the panel
./startpanel
```

### System-wide Installation
```bash
# Install dependencies (Ubuntu/Debian)
sudo apt install python3-gi python3-gi-cairo gir1.2-gtk-3.0 \
    python3-pip python3-setuptools python3-wheel \
    gtk2-engines-pixbuf imagemagick qt5ct \
    qt5-style-plugins lxqt-config openbox

# Install Python dependencies
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

# Optional: Install system-wide
sudo python3 setup.py install
```

## Usage

Configuration of the cdepanel app can mostly be done by right
click on the panel. Different options will be shown when clicking
on a launcher (icon), drawer, or side handle. 

Apps can be added to the panel and drawers using drag and drop.
One can drag icons over from the xfce4-appfinder or whisker menu
to the panel or open drawer. But one can also drag icons from an
open drawer to the panel or vice versa, or from one position in
the panel to another.

Colors, backdrops and window borders can be changed  in the
'Settings' dialog (right-click panel). More advanced settings can
be made by editing the config file (see 'Advanced' tab in the
settings dialog). Edit at your own risk! 

Keys and mouse on panel:

mousewheel:				Switch workspace
=/-, ctrl-mousewheel:	Larger/smaller size
h/H, shift-mousewheel:	More/less sharpness
p/P:		Cycle back/forth through color palettes 
s/S:		More/less saturated colors in panel
c:			Pop up config dialog
r:			Save layout (after moving buttons etc)
n:			Toggle between 4 and 8 colors mode
esc:		Close all drawers
ctrl-c:		Exit program
ctrl-r: 	Restart
0: 			Resize panel to unscaled 'original' size

Mousewheel over pavucontrol icon: change speaker volume.
Mouse at bottom of the screen raises the panel window above all
others.


## Theme Management

### Theme Customization Methods

#### 1. Modern Theming System (Recommended)
The new theming system provides better performance and reliability:

- **GUI Configuration**: Right-click on the panel and select 'Settings'
- **Config File**: Edit `~/.config/cdetheme/config.ini`
- **Command Line**: Use `cdepanel --help` for available options

#### 2. Legacy `switchtheme` Script
For backward compatibility, the original `switchtheme` script is still available:

```bash
# Basic usage
./scripts/switchtheme palettes/YourTheme.dp 8 3 20 true true true

# Example: HP-UX style
./scripts/switchtheme palettes/Broica.dp 8 3 22 true true true

# Example: Solaris style
./scripts/switchtheme palettes/Crimson.dp 4 3 20 true true true
```

**Note**: While still functional, the `switchtheme` script is considered legacy. New features and improvements will focus on the modern theming system.

### Migrating from switchtheme to the New System

If you were previously using `switchtheme`, you can migrate your settings:

1. Your existing themes in `~/.themes/cdetheme/` will continue to work
2. The new system will automatically detect and use these themes
3. For new themes, consider using the modern theming system for better performance and features

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `CDE_THEME` | Theme name to use | `default` |
| `CDE_CACHE_DIR` | Cache directory | `~/.cache/cdetheme` |
| `GTK_THEME` | GTK theme to use | `CDE` |
| `QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME` | Qt platform theme | `qt5ct` |

## Qt5 Support

For Qt5 applications to use the CDE theme, install qt5ct and configure it:

1. Install qt5ct and Qt5 style plugins:
   sudo apt install qt5ct qt5-style-plugins

2. Set the environment variable in your ~/.bashrc:
   export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt5ct

3. Run qt5ct and select "gtk+" as the style to match the GTK theme

This will make Qt5 applications use the same visual style as GTK applications.

## Troubleshooting

### Theme Compatibility

#### Using switchtheme with the New System
- Themes created with `switchtheme` are fully compatible with the new system
- The new system adds caching and better error handling for these themes
- When using both systems, the new system's settings will take precedence

### Common Issues

1. **Theme not applying**
   - Ensure all dependencies are installed
   - Check logs in `~/.cache/cdetheme/cdepanel.log`
   - Try running with `--debug` flag for more verbose output

2. **Missing Icons**
   - Install the required icon theme
   - Check icon theme path in settings

3. **Performance Issues**
   - Clear cache: `rm -rf ~/.cache/cdetheme/*`
   - Disable unnecessary theme components

## Legacy Documentation

### switchtheme Reference

#### Usage
```
./switchtheme paletteFile nrOfColors borderWidth titleHeight useWindowDecorations useGtkTheme useBackDrops
```

#### Arguments
- `paletteFile`: Path to CDE color palette (e.g., `palettes/Broica.dp`)
- `nrOfColors`: Number of colors (4 or 8)
- `borderWidth`: Window border width in pixels
- `titleHeight`: Window title bar height in pixels
- `useWindowDecorations`: `true`/`false` to apply window decorations
- `useGtkTheme`: `true`/`false` to apply GTK theme
- `useBackDrops`: `true`/`false` to apply desktop backgrounds

#### Example Palettes
- `Broica.dp`: Classic HP-UX style
- `Crimson.dp`: Solaris-inspired theme
- `Africa.dp`: Earth tones
- `Alpine.dp`: Cool blue tones

